# Code-Agent ðŸš€
## Use `codex` command to automate software development workflows. âœ¨

HiðŸ‘‹  I'm Shingo Morimoto, an University student in Japan. I'm so interested in creating LLM application using LangChain. 

The `codex` command,including subcommands: gen-commit, gen-readme, describe, suggest-comment, suggest-code, is a powerful tool to integrate your code with LLM power.âœ¨
Currently, you can execute `codex gen-commit` to automate the creation of Git commit message from diff between HEAD commit and index.

## ðŸŒŸ Getting Started



### Install code-agent with pip ðŸ“: 

To use the codex command anywhere install it with pip:

`pip install code-agent` or `pip install --break-system-packages code-agent ` if you are using newer pip. 


###  **Usage** ðŸš€:

Amazing! Now you can use `codex` command anywhere!
```
$ codex --help

